{
 "response": "# Perspective Audit \u2014 Image Gallery With Undersized Touch Targets\n\n## Step 1 \u2014 Escalated perspectives confirmed\n\nFrom the a11y-critic escalation:\n\n- **Magnification & Reflow \u2014 HIGH** \u2192 deep review\n- **Keyboard & Motor Access \u2014 MEDIUM** \u2192 deep review\n\nPerspectives at LOW / not escalated (Environmental Contrast, Vestibular & Motion, Auditory Access, Screen Reader & Semantic, Cognitive & Neurodivergent) are **not** reviewed. Where a finding in an escalated perspective has an obvious adjacency into a non-escalated one (e.g., focus-contrast under Environmental Contrast), it is flagged for human verification rather than deep-audited.\n\n## Step 2 \u2014 Reference files\n\n- `references/perspectives.md` \u2014 loaded sections **1 (Magnification & Reflow)** and **5 (Keyboard & Motor Access)** only.\n- `references/arrm-perspective-mapping.md` \u2014 loaded in full; per-finding routing applied via the decision tree.\n\n## Step 3 \u2014 Artifact reviewed\n\nSingle React component `ImageGallery` (JSX + CSS inline in the fixture). Structure: a `<section>` gallery with a 9-item `<button>` thumbnail grid, and a conditional lightbox `role=\"dialog\" aria-modal=\"true\"` containing the full image, a close button, prev/next buttons, and a zoom control pair. All controls are native `<button>` elements. Source-only review \u2014 no browser, no visual regression, no live keyboard walkthrough. Screenshot-dependent claims are marked for human verification.\n\n---\n\n## Step 4 \u2014 Per-perspective checklists\n\n### Perspective 1 \u2014 Magnification & Reflow (HIGH)\n\n| # | JTBD item (WCAG) | Result |\n|---|---|---|\n| 1 | Reflows to single column at 320px, no horizontal scrollbar (1.4.10) | **FINDING** (F1) \u2014 lightbox prev/next clip off-screen. Thumbnail grid itself reflows (see calibration note). |\n| 2 | Focused elements never obscured by sticky/fixed elements (2.4.11) | **FINDING** \u2014 manifests via F2 (background focus lands behind the fixed overlay) and F1 (prev/next focus clipped beyond the viewport at zoom). |\n| 3 | Text scales to 200% without overflow/truncation (1.4.4) | **FINDING** (F5) |\n| 4 | Adapts to text-spacing overrides (1.4.12) | **FINDING** (F5) |\n| 5 | Hover/focus content dismissible, hoverable, persistent (1.4.13) | **N/A** \u2014 no tooltips/popovers; `aria-label` only, no visual hover content. |\n\n**Red flags checked:** Two-axis scrolling at 320px \u2014 does **not** cleanly fire: the overlay is `position: fixed`, so the mispositioned prev/next controls are *clipped by the viewport* rather than producing a second scroll axis (arguably worse \u2014 the control becomes unreachable by pointer, see F1). Text hidden/overlapping at 200% \u2014 glyphs overflow but are not fully hidden (F5, MINOR). Tooltip vanishing \u2014 N/A. **No auto-CRITICAL red flag fires.**\n\n### Perspective 5 \u2014 Keyboard & Motor Access (MEDIUM)\n\n| # | JTBD item (WCAG) | Result |\n|---|---|---|\n| 1 | All interactive elements keyboard reachable/operable (2.1.1) | **PASS** \u2014 every control is a native `<button>`; Enter/Space operate them. |\n| 2 | No keyboard trap (2.1.2) | **PASS** \u2014 no trap. Note: the *opposite* defect exists (focus escapes the modal \u2014 see F2). |\n| 3 | Skip link targets main content (2.4.1) | **N/A** \u2014 component scope, not a full page. |\n| 4 | Focus order logical (2.4.3) | **FINDING** (F2) \u2014 modal does not contain Tab; order leaks to background. |\n| 5 | Focus indicator \u22652px, \u22653:1 contrast (2.4.7) | **PASS (with caveat)** \u2014 every control has a `:focus-visible` outline (\u22652px); no `outline:none`. White-on-image contrast for close/zoom/nav rings is image-dependent \u2192 verification note. (2.4.13 Focus Appearance is AAA \u2192 ENHANCEMENT E2.) |\n| 6 | Multi-point gestures have single-pointer alt (2.5.1) | **PASS** \u2014 zoom is button-driven; no pinch/multi-finger. |\n| 7 | Activation on up-event (2.5.2) | **PASS** \u2014 `onClick` (click = up-event; abortable). |\n| 8 | Label in Name (2.5.3) | **PASS** \u2014 icon-only buttons carry `aria-label`; no visible text label to mismatch. Minor voice-control discoverability note (E-level). |\n| 9 | Every drag has a click alternative (2.5.7) | **N/A** \u2014 no drag interactions. |\n| 10 | Targets \u226524\u00d724 CSS px with adequate spacing (2.5.8) | **FINDING** \u2014 close 16\u00d716 (F3), zoom pair 20\u00d720 (F4). Thumbnails 32\u00d732 **PASS**; prev/next ~48px tall **PASS**. |\n| 11 | Portrait and landscape both supported (1.3.4) | **PASS** \u2014 no orientation lock. |\n\n**Red flags checked:** Element unreachable by keyboard \u2014 none. Keyboard trap \u2014 none. Drag-only interaction \u2014 none. `outline:none` with no replacement \u2014 **not present** (all controls have `:focus-visible`). **No auto-CRITICAL red flag fires.**\n\n---\n\n## Calibration notes \u2014 two planted comments that misapply their criteria\n\nThe fixture carries inline comments that overstate or misstate the violation. Naming them is part of the review; a critic that simply echoes the comments is doing dead work.\n\n1. **\"Thumbnails are 32\u00d732px with 2px gap \u2026 2.5.8 \u2026 adjacent targets overlap effective hit area.\"** This misapplies 2.5.8. Target Size (Minimum) is satisfied outright when the target is **\u226524\u00d724 CSS px** \u2014 spacing only matters as an *exception path for undersized (<24px) targets*. At 32\u00d732 the thumbnails **pass 2.5.8 on size**, and the 2px gap is irrelevant to the criterion. The thumbnails are the *least* of this component's target-size problems; the real offenders are the 16px close and 20px zoom controls inside the lightbox.\n\n2. **\"At 200% zoom, grid overflows horizontally \u2026 no flex-wrap or responsive breakpoint.\"** The grid is `grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, 32px)`. `auto-fill` with a fixed track size **is** a reflow mechanism \u2014 it lays as many 32px columns as fit and wraps the rest. Under standard browser zoom the thumbnail grid reflows without a horizontal scrollbar. The genuine 1.4.10 failure is **not** the grid \u2014 it is the lightbox prev/next controls positioned at negative offsets outside the content box (F1).\n\nBoth corrections *narrow* the finding set to what a real magnifier/motor user actually hits, rather than inflating severity to match the comments.\n\n---\n\n## Step 5 \u2014 Findings\n\n**Finding:** Lightbox previous/next controls are positioned outside the content box (`left: -48px` / `right: -48px`). At a 320px-equivalent viewport (400% zoom) the content is `90vw \u2248 288px`, leaving ~16px of total horizontal margin \u2014 far less than the 48px offset plus the button's own ~40\u201350px width. The controls are pushed past the viewport edge and, because the overlay is `position: fixed`, are *clipped* rather than scrollable, making prev/next pointer-unreachable at high zoom / narrow widths. A focused prev/next also sits off-screen (its focus ring is not visible).\n**WCAG:** 1.4.10 Reflow (secondary: 2.4.11 Focus Not Obscured \u2014 Minimum)\n**Perspective:** Magnification & Reflow\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** Visual Design (secondary: Front-End Dev)\n**Evidence:** CSS `.lightbox-prev { left: -48px; }`, `.lightbox-next { right: -48px; }`, `.lightbox-content { max-width: 90vw; }`; overlay `.lightbox-overlay { position: fixed; }`. Fixture comment: \"lightbox-prev/next positioned at viewport edge \u2014 clipped at zoom.\"\n**Fix:** Position prev/next *inside* the content box (e.g., `left: 8px` / `right: 8px`, overlaid on the image with a scrim) or in a controls bar within the 90vw content. Verify at 320px / 400% zoom that both controls remain fully on-screen and their focus ring is visible.\n**Verification:** Visual regression at 200% and 400% zoom currently unavailable \u2014 confirm on-screen presence with a screenshot pass.\n\n---\n\n**Finding:** The lightbox does not contain keyboard focus. The `useEffect` sets initial focus to the close button and handles Escape, but there is **no Tab/Shift+Tab containment**. Because `aria-modal=\"true\"` does not constrain the Tab sequence (only AT virtual-cursor behavior), one Shift+Tab from the close button \u2014 or Tab past the last control (zoom-out) \u2014 moves focus to the thumbnail grid, which is still in the DOM behind the overlay. The focused thumbnail is then entirely hidden under the `rgba(0,0,0,0.9)` overlay, so the keyboard user loses all visible indication of where focus is. This directly contradicts the fixture comment \"Focus trap and Escape handling \u2014 correctly implemented\": Escape and initial focus are implemented; the trap is not.\n**WCAG:** 2.4.3 Focus Order (secondary: 2.4.11 Focus Not Obscured \u2014 Minimum; dialog-pattern dimension is 4.1.2, in the non-escalated Screen Reader perspective)\n**Perspective:** Keyboard & Motor Access\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: UX Design)\n**Evidence:** JSX lines 47\u201355 `useEffect` handles only `Escape` + `closeBtnRef.current?.focus()`; no `keydown` Tab handler and no focus sentinels; thumbnail `<button>`s (lines 69\u201377) remain focusable in the DOM behind `.lightbox-overlay` (`z-index: 1000`, `background: rgba(0,0,0,0.9)`).\n**Fix:** Implement real focus containment: trap Tab/Shift+Tab within the dialog (wrap-around at first/last focusable), or set `inert`/`aria-hidden` + remove tabbability on the background gallery while the lightbox is open. Re-verify that Tab cycles only through close \u2192 prev \u2192 next \u2192 zoom-in \u2192 zoom-out.\n\n---\n\n**Finding:** The lightbox close button is **16\u00d716 CSS px**, below the 24\u00d724 minimum, and is the primary pointer-driven dismissal control. It is spatially isolated (nearest targets \u2014 prev/next at vertical center, zoom at bottom-right \u2014 are >24px away), so it *may technically satisfy 2.5.8 via the undersized-target spacing exception*. Per severity calibration (impact on people, not rule weight), a 16px dismiss target is a real barrier for users with tremor, low dexterity, or who rely on head-pointer/eye-gaze/switch pointing. Escape mitigates for keyboard users but **not** for pointer-only motor users.\n**WCAG:** 2.5.8 Target Size (Minimum)\n**Perspective:** Keyboard & Motor Access\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** Visual Design (secondary: Front-End Dev)\n**Evidence:** CSS `.lightbox-close { width: 16px; height: 16px; top: 4px; right: 4px; }`. Fixture comment: \"Close button is 16x16px \u2014 WCAG 2.5.8.\"\n**Fix:** Enlarge the close button to \u226524\u00d724 (44\u00d744 recommended, see E1). Keep the visual glyph size if desired but expand the hit area via padding.\n\n---\n\n**Finding:** The zoom in/out controls are **20\u00d720 CSS px** in a flex row with `gap: 4px`. Both are undersized (<24px) **and** adjacent, so the spacing exception is at best borderline (center-to-center \u2248 24px \u2014 tangent, not comfortably clear). Two small, tightly packed controls that perform *opposite* actions (zoom in vs. zoom out) create a high mis-tap risk for motor-impaired users.\n**WCAG:** 2.5.8 Target Size (Minimum)\n**Perspective:** Keyboard & Motor Access\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** Visual Design (secondary: Front-End Dev)\n**Evidence:** CSS `.zoom-btn { width: 20px; height: 20px; }`, `.zoom-controls { display: flex; gap: 4px; }`. Fixture comment: \"Zoom buttons are 20x20px \u2014 WCAG 2.5.8.\"\n**Fix:** Size each zoom control to \u226524\u00d724 (44\u00d744 recommended) and increase inter-control spacing to \u226524px offset so the two opposite actions cannot be confused by an imprecise pointer.\n\n---\n\n**Finding:** Fixed-pixel icon buttons clip their glyphs when text is scaled or text-spacing is overridden. The close button is 16\u00d716 with `font-size: 14px; line-height: 16px`; the zoom buttons are 20\u00d720 with `font-size: 14px`. Under 200% text-only zoom the glyph renders at ~28px inside a 16\u201320px box, and a 1.4.12 line-height override (1.5\u00d7) forces ~21px line height into the 16px close box \u2014 both overflow/clip the container because the box dimensions are fixed and do not grow with text. (Under whole-page browser zoom the box scales too, so impact is limited to the text-only / user-stylesheet path.)\n**WCAG:** 1.4.4 Resize Text (secondary: 1.4.12 Text Spacing)\n**Perspective:** Magnification & Reflow\n**Severity:** MINOR\n**Route to:** Visual Design (secondary: Front-End Dev)\n**Evidence:** CSS `.lightbox-close { width: 16px; height: 16px; font-size: 14px; line-height: 16px; }`, `.zoom-btn { width: 20px; height: 20px; font-size: 14px; }`.\n**Fix:** Use `min-width`/`min-height` with padding and unitless or `em` line-height so containers grow with text; avoid pinning both box size and line-height in px. Enlarging the controls per F3/F4 largely resolves this as a side effect.\n\n---\n\n**Finding:** The zoom feature scales the image via `transform: scale()` up to 3\u00d7, but the lightbox provides no pan/scroll affordance. A `transform`-scaled image overflows the `.lightbox-content` box (which has no `overflow` handling) and can extend beyond the viewport, so a low-vision user who zooms in cannot reach the edges of the enlarged image \u2014 the portion they zoomed to inspect may be off-screen with no in-dialog way to move to it.\n**WCAG:** 1.4.10 Reflow\n**Perspective:** Magnification & Reflow\n**Severity:** MINOR\n**Route to:** UX Design (secondary: Front-End Dev)\n**Evidence:** JSX `<img \u2026 style={{ transform: `scale(${zoom})` }} />`; CSS `.lightbox-content` and `.lightbox-content img` set no `overflow`/pan mechanism; `setZoom` ranges 0.5\u20133.\n**Fix:** Wrap the zoomed image in a scrollable/pannable container (e.g., `overflow: auto` with keyboard-operable pan, or drag-to-pan *with* a keyboard/button alternative per 2.5.7) so the enlarged region is reachable. **[Human verification required \u2014 exact overflow/scroll behavior at scale(3) needs a browser check.]**\n\n---\n\n**Enhancements (AAA \u2014 reported, never escalated):**\n\n**E1 \u2014 Target Size (Enhanced):** Close (16px), zoom (20px), and even the 32px thumbnails fall below the 44\u00d744 target recommended by **2.5.5 Target Size (Enhanced), AAA**. Adopting 44\u00d744 for all controls would resolve F3/F4 and E1 together. Route: Visual Design.\n\n**E2 \u2014 Focus Appearance:** The 2px white `:focus-visible` outlines on the close, zoom, and nav buttons may not meet the minimum-area and 3:1 contrast expectations of **2.4.13 Focus Appearance, AAA** when the ring falls over a light region of the image. Route: Visual Design. **[Human verification required \u2014 image-dependent contrast.]**\n\n---\n\n## Step 5 (contract) \u2014 A11y Evidence Findings for MAJOR results\n\n```\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: reflow-lightbox-nav-offscreen\nfingerprint: 7b3e9c2a1f4d8065\nsource: perspective-audit Magnification & Reflow checklist\nwcag_or_apg: 1.4.10 Reflow (2.4.11 Focus Not Obscured \u2014 Minimum)\nsection_508_fpc_context: not in scope (2.5.8/2.4.11/1.4.10 are WCAG 2.1/2.2, post-dating the Section 508 WCAG 2.0 baseline)\nseverity: MAJOR\nperspective_alarms: magnification_reflow=HIGH, keyboard_motor=MEDIUM\nevidence: CSS .lightbox-prev{left:-48px} / .lightbox-next{right:-48px} within .lightbox-content{max-width:90vw} under fixed overlay\nreproduction_steps: source review only; confirm at 400% zoom / 320px-equivalent width in browser\nexpected_behavior: prev/next remain fully on-screen and focus-visible at 320px equivalent\nactual_behavior: controls positioned outside the 90vw content box are clipped past the fixed-overlay viewport edge and become pointer-unreachable\ntrend: new\n```\n\n```\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: dialog-focus-not-contained\nfingerprint: a1c8f042e9b7d3a6\nsource: perspective-audit Keyboard & Motor Access checklist\nwcag_or_apg: 2.4.3 Focus Order; WAI-ARIA APG Dialog (Modal) pattern \u2014 focus containment\nsection_508_fpc_context: Revised Section 508 incorporates WCAG 2.0 2.4.3 (A) \u2014 applicable\nseverity: MAJOR\nperspective_alarms: keyboard_motor=MEDIUM, magnification_reflow=HIGH (focus obscured by overlay)\nevidence: JSX useEffect (lines 47-55) sets initial focus + Escape only; no Tab containment; background thumbnail buttons remain focusable behind .lightbox-overlay (z-index:1000, rgba(0,0,0,0.9))\nreproduction_steps: source review only; open lightbox, press Shift+Tab (or Tab past zoom-out), observe focus land on a background thumbnail hidden under the overlay\nexpected_behavior: Tab/Shift+Tab cycle only among the dialog's controls\nactual_behavior: focus escapes to the obscured background gallery; no visible focus indication\ntrend: new\n```\n\n```\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: close-button-target-size\nfingerprint: 3f9d1e7c04ab8256\nsource: perspective-audit Keyboard & Motor Access checklist\nwcag_or_apg: 2.5.8 Target Size (Minimum)\nsection_508_fpc_context: not in scope (2.5.8 is WCAG 2.2, post-dates the Section 508 WCAG 2.0 baseline)\nseverity: MAJOR\nperspective_alarms: keyboard_motor=MEDIUM\nevidence: CSS .lightbox-close{width:16px;height:16px}\nreproduction_steps: source review only; measure rendered close-button box\nexpected_behavior: primary dismiss control is >=24x24 (ideally 44x44) CSS px\nactual_behavior: 16x16 target; may pass 2.5.8 via isolation/spacing exception but is a real motor barrier for pointer-only users (Escape does not help them)\ntrend: new\n```\n\n```\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: zoom-buttons-target-size\nfingerprint: c62b90a4d1e8f371\nsource: perspective-audit Keyboard & Motor Access checklist\nwcag_or_apg: 2.5.8 Target Size (Minimum)\nsection_508_fpc_context: not in scope (2.5.8 is WCAG 2.2)\nseverity: MAJOR\nperspective_alarms: keyboard_motor=MEDIUM\nevidence: CSS .zoom-btn{width:20px;height:20px}; .zoom-controls{display:flex;gap:4px}\nreproduction_steps: source review only; measure the two zoom controls and their offset\nexpected_behavior: each control >=24x24 with >=24px offset between adjacent opposite-action controls\nactual_behavior: 20x20 undersized controls at ~24px center-to-center (borderline spacing) performing opposite actions; high mis-tap risk\ntrend: new\n```\n\n---\n\n## Step 6 \u2014 Perspective Audit Summary\n\n**Component/artifact reviewed:** ImageGallery (React thumbnail grid + lightbox)\n**Perspectives escalated for deep review:** Magnification & Reflow (HIGH); Keyboard & Motor Access (MEDIUM)\n**Perspectives at LOW (not reviewed):** Environmental Contrast; Vestibular & Motion; Auditory Access; Screen Reader & Semantic Structure; Cognitive & Neurodivergent\n\n### Findings by Severity\n\n| Severity | Count |\n|---|---|\n| CRITICAL | 0 |\n| MAJOR | 4 |\n| MINOR | 2 |\n| ENHANCEMENT | 2 |\n\n### Perspectives That Passed\n\nNone fully passed \u2014 both escalated perspectives produced findings. Within them, the following JTBD items passed cleanly: keyboard reachability/operability (2.1.1), no keyboard trap (2.1.2), up-event activation (2.5.2), single-pointer zoom (2.5.1), no drag (2.5.7), orientation (1.3.4), label-in-name (2.5.3), and focus-indicator presence (2.4.7). The thumbnail grid passed both 2.5.8 (32\u00d732 \u2265 minimum) and 1.4.10 reflow (auto-fill wraps) \u2014 contrary to the fixture's inline comments.\n\n### Perspectives With Findings \u2014 Grouped by ARRM Role\n\n**Front-End Dev**\n- Modal dialog does not contain keyboard focus \u2014 Keyboard & Motor \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 2.4.3 Focus Order\n\n**Visual Design**\n- Lightbox prev/next positioned off the content box, clipped at zoom \u2014 Magnification & Reflow \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 1.4.10 Reflow\n- Close button 16\u00d716px below minimum target size \u2014 Keyboard & Motor \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 2.5.8 Target Size (Minimum)\n- Zoom controls 20\u00d720px, undersized and tightly spaced \u2014 Keyboard & Motor \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 2.5.8 Target Size (Minimum)\n- Fixed-px icon buttons clip glyphs at 200% text zoom / spacing overrides \u2014 Magnification & Reflow \u2014 MINOR \u2014 1.4.4 / 1.4.12\n- Target Size (Enhanced) 44\u00d744 not met \u2014 Keyboard & Motor \u2014 ENHANCEMENT \u2014 2.5.5 (AAA)\n- Focus Appearance area/contrast on light images \u2014 Keyboard & Motor \u2014 ENHANCEMENT \u2014 2.4.13 (AAA)\n\n**UX Design**\n- Zoom-scaled image overflows lightbox with no pan/scroll affordance \u2014 Magnification & Reflow \u2014 MINOR \u2014 1.4.10 Reflow\n\n**Content Author**\n- None.\n\n### Open Questions Requiring Human Verification\n\n- Visual regression at 200% and 400% zoom to confirm prev/next clip off-screen and that the grid does not (F1).\n- Browser check of `transform: scale(3)` overflow behavior and whether a page-level scrollbar appears (F6).\n- Focus-ring contrast of the 2px white outlines over light regions of the displayed images (2.4.7 caveat / E2) \u2014 image-dependent, cannot be confirmed from source.\n\n### Recommended Next Step\n\n**REVISE** \u2014 4 MAJOR findings, no CRITICAL. The component's ARIA scaffolding (real buttons, `role=\"dialog\"`, `aria-modal`, initial focus, Escape, focus return, disabled boundary states) is sound, but it must not ship until the MAJOR findings are addressed: (1) contain modal focus, (2) reposition prev/next inside the content box, (3) enlarge the close button to \u226524\u00d724, and (4) enlarge and space the zoom controls. Priority order: F2 (focus containment) and F1 (nav clipping) first \u2014 they affect task completion at zoom and by keyboard \u2014 then F3/F4 target sizing. Re-run a11y-test (keyboard walkthrough + zoom/reflow screenshots) after the fixes.\n",
